“A Dockerfile defines how to build a Docker image. It typically starts with a base image,
FROM (base image)
sets a working directory,
WORKDIR (set path)
e.g. 
WORKDIR /app 
copies dependencies,
COPY dependencies
e.g.
COPY npm
installs them,
RUN npm install
copies application code,
COPY code
and defines the startup command using CMD. 
CMD ["echo" , "write your message"]
Proper ordering ensures efficient layer caching and faster builds.”


🧠 1. What is a Dockerfile?

“A Dockerfile is a set of instructions used to build a Docker image.”

🔄 Flow
Dockerfile → docker build → Image → docker run → Container
🧠 2. Core Instructions (YOU MUST KNOW)
🔹 FROM
FROM ubuntu

👉 Base image (starting point)

🔹 WORKDIR
WORKDIR /app

👉 Sets working directory inside container

🔹 COPY
COPY . .

👉 Copies files into container

🔹 RUN
RUN apt update && apt install -y curl

👉 Runs commands during build time

🔹 CMD
CMD ["node", "app.js"]

👉 Runs command when container starts

🧠 3. RUN vs CMD (CRITICAL)
RUN	CMD
Build time	Runtime
Install/setup	Start app
Runs once	Runs every container start
🧠 4. Execution Types
🔹 Exec form (preferred)
CMD ["node", "app.js"]
🔹 Shell form
CMD sh -c "echo hello && sleep 5"

👉 Needed for multiple commands

🧠 5. Layer & Caching (VERY IMPORTANT)
❌ Bad
COPY . .
RUN npm install

👉 Any change → reinstall ❌

✅ Good
COPY package.json .
RUN npm install
COPY . .

👉 Faster builds ✔️

🧠 6. Container Lifecycle

👉 Container runs while:

main process is running
❌ Example
CMD ["echo", "hello"]

👉 Exits immediately

✅ Example
CMD ["sleep", "1000"]

👉 Stays alive

🧠 7. Multiple Commands
❌ Wrong
CMD ["echo", "hi", "sleep", "5"]
✅ Correct
CMD sh -c "echo hi && sleep 5"
🧠 8. Best Practices (INTERVIEW GOLD)
🔥 Combine RUN commands
RUN apt update && apt install -y curl
🔥 Use WORKDIR

👉 Avoid messy root (/)

🔥 Use correct CMD

👉 Always run main app

🔥 Use caching properly

👉 Copy dependencies first

🧠 9. Common Issues + Fix
🔴 Container exits

👉 Missing CMD / no process

🔴 Command not found

👉 Dependency not installed

🔴 Build slow

👉 Bad caching order

🔴 App not accessible

👉 Port / binding issue


🧱 Core Dockerfile Components (with Syntax)
1. FROM – Base Image
FROM ubuntu:22.04
Starting point of your image
Must be the first instruction
Can be used multiple times (multi-stage builds)
2. WORKDIR – Set Working Directory
WORKDIR /app
Like cd /app
Creates directory if it doesn’t exist
All next commands run from here
3. COPY – Copy Files from Local → Container
COPY . /app
COPY requirements.txt .
Simple file copy
Uses .dockerignore
4. ADD – Advanced Copy (rarely needed)
ADD app.tar.gz /app
ADD https://example.com/file.txt /app
Can extract archives
Can download URLs
❗ Prefer COPY unless you need these features
5. RUN – Execute Commands (Build Time)
RUN apt update && apt install -y curl
Runs during image build
Creates a new layer

💡 Best practice:

RUN apt update && apt install -y curl && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
6. CMD – Default Command (Runtime)
CMD ["python", "app.py"]

OR

CMD python app.py
Runs when container starts
Can be overridden:
docker run image_name bash
7. ENTRYPOINT – Fixed Command
ENTRYPOINT ["python"]

Combine with CMD:

ENTRYPOINT ["python"]
CMD ["app.py"]

👉 Final execution:

python app.py
⚡ CMD vs ENTRYPOINT (Important)
Feature	CMD	ENTRYPOINT
Overridable	✅ Yes	❌ No (by default)
Use case	Default command	Fixed behavior
Combination	Works together	Preferred combo
8. ENV – Environment Variables
ENV APP_ENV=production
ENV PORT=5000
Available at runtime
Used inside app
9. ARG – Build-time Variables
ARG VERSION=1.0

Usage:

RUN echo $VERSION

Build:

docker build --build-arg VERSION=2.0 .

👉 Difference:

ARG → build time only
ENV → runtime
10. EXPOSE – Document Port
EXPOSE 5000
Just documentation
Does NOT open port

Actual run:

docker run -p 5000:5000 image
11. VOLUME – Persistent Storage
VOLUME ["/data"]
Creates mount point
Data survives container deletion
12. USER – Run as Non-root
USER appuser
Security best practice
Avoid root containers
13. LABEL – Metadata
LABEL version="1.0"
LABEL maintainer="kiran"
14. SHELL – Change Default Shell
SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
15. HEALTHCHECK – Container Health
HEALTHCHECK CMD curl --fail http://localhost:5000 || exit 1
Used in production
Docker checks container health
16. ONBUILD – Trigger on Child Image
ONBUILD COPY . /app
Runs when used as base image
Advanced use case
17. Multi-stage Build (VERY IMPORTANT)
FROM node:18 AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN npm install

FROM node:18-slim
COPY --from=builder /app /app
CMD ["node", "app.js"]

👉 Reduces image size

🧠 Order Matters (Best Practice Structure)
FROM image

WORKDIR /app

COPY package.json .
RUN npm install

COPY . .

ENV PORT=3000

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["node", "app.js"]
⚠️ Common Mistakes (You should avoid)

❌ Too many RUN layers
❌ Using ADD unnecessarily
❌ Running as root
❌ Not using .dockerignore
❌ Copying everything before installing dependencies

🔥 Quick Mental Model
FROM → Base
RUN → Build setup
COPY → Bring code
ENV → Config
CMD/ENTRYPOINT → Run app
